feat: script Room 4 "Silence" and fix stairs hallway headroom

Room 4 is now a pinned silence milestone:
- New 'silence' scripted theme at SCRIPTED_THEMES index 3 with terse
  signage and a muted palette.
- Ambient audio engine hard-mutes the master bus on 'silence' and
  restores it on exit, replacing the drone bed with genuine silence.
- SilenceArtifact centerpiece: a matte-black briefcase sitting ajar on
  the plinth, a pencil beam of cold white light escaping the gap, and
  a frozen snapshot of twelve pages hanging in mid-fall around it.
- SilenceWatchers: a ring of nine Faceless Suit figures that yaw-track
  the camera every frame, positioned to avoid the doorway axis. Each
  gets a tight head fill light so they never disappear against the
  dark walls.

Stairs hallway overhaul:
- The ascending and descending ceiling planes had inverted tilts,
  which pinched headroom to ~1.4m at the plateau seams and exposed
  the underside of the single-sided planes, letting the player see
  outside the museum. Replaced the tilted ceilings with a single
  flat thick slab at plateau + RAMP_CEILING, overlapping the side
  walls so no seam is ever visible.
- Raised RAMP_CEILING 4.2 -> 5.2 for noticeably more headroom on
  every step of the climb.
- Side walls now extend slightly past the ceiling slab and the
  dead-end cap matches the new full height.
